summary:
▪ My Medium, Telegram, Twitter and Clubhouse: @smehikudri 
▪ Languages: Russian – native; Armenian – native; English – advanced; Italian – advanced; French – intermediate; German – intermediate; Portuguese – elementary

My achievements:
▪ I helped relaunch & revise CN Traveller Russia's website in 2016. Thanks to my contribution the traffic has tripled in 6 months (it went from 250 000 unique users to 750 000)
▪ I helped launch InStyle Russia's website in 2017. In the first year it made to the top 10 glossy magazines in the country by traffic. 
▪ When IKEA launched its first streetwear collection for millennials SPANST in Russia, I helped make it reach over 45 million people. 

My awards:
▪ As part of the Mint Agency BBDO Group team won IPRA Golden Award for the best ‘Launch of the new product’ (IKEA Spanst collection)
▪ As part of the Contrast Foundry Design Studio's team won Communication Arts Awards in Typography category for the CoFo Farm Specimen

projects:
[{'title': 'CoFo Farm Specimen creation ', 'date': {'start': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}, 'end': {'month': 12, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, 'description': "Project: CoFo Farm Specimen creation 

Scope: To create an original specimen to promote the work of the type design studio

My role: Text Chief

Stakeholders: Type Designers

Goal: To convey all of the studio's history, tools and typefaces in a unique and entertaining form

Process: In the spring of 2019, the Contrast Foundry team asked me to help them create a very special and not at all traditional specimen. Guys came up with a sipid metaphor: they associated the whole process of fonts creation with organic farming, their fonts—with vegetables and fruits and themselves—with farmers.
 
We took inspiration from classic agricultural magazines and made a magazine full of useful information, tips about farming, recipes with the mentioned fruits and vegetables, and even a crossword puzzle and sudoku for the readers to have some fun. And all of it with hints and references to the type design. 

Results: The specimen had success and was sent out to Canada, France, United Kingdom, Germany, Japan, USA and got picked up by AIGA Eye On Design in New York—a magazine that writes about the best new work by the world's most exciting designers. ", 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Susa', 'last_name': 'Agababyan', 'name': None, 'headline': 'UX Writer at Booking.com'}]}, {'title': 'IKEA 75 Celebration', 'date': {'start': {'month': 8, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}, 'end': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}}, 'description': "Project: IKEA's 75 Birthday

Scope: In autumn 2018 IKEA was celebrating its 75th Birthday worldwide. In Russia the team of Instinct creative agency launched a large scale ‘Thank you’ campaign to thank all of the brand’s customers for their affection and loyalty. 

My role: Project Manager

Stakeholders: Marketing Director IKEA Russia, PR and Product Promotion Manager for IKEA Russia, SM Manager IKEA Russia, lead designers from Instinct

Goal: To conduct a series of federal and regional events and get the max. coverage

Results: 300 guests at the kick-off party—journalists, bloggers, interior designers and IKEA Family members. Among those who came there were representatives of Vogue, Forbes, InStyle, Elle Decoration, The Blueprint, Vedomosti and popular bloggers @katrinka_family (1 million subscribers), @dmitrykrikun (333K subscribers), @alex.mazurov (275K subscribers) and others; the number of publications in traditional media reached 140, and the number of stories posted by bloggers—330 with an approximate reach of 1,053,638.", 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Susa', 'last_name': 'Agababyan', 'name': None, 'headline': 'UX Writer at Booking.com'}]}, {'title': 'IKEA SPANST Collection Launch', 'date': {'start': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}, 'end': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}}, 'description': "Project: IKEA SPANST Collection Launch

Scope: To create an unusual promotion for such an unusual range: SPANST was the first limited collection created by IKEA specially for Millenials and consisted of transparent shoe boxes, hoodies, a skateboard and other non-conventional pieces

Challenges: According to IKEA’s research Millenials didn't buy their items.

My role: Project Manager

Stakeholders: Marketing Director IKEA Russia, PR and Product Promotion Manager for IKEA Russia, SM Manager IKEA Russia

Goal: Attract Millenials to the IKEA shops

Process: We decided to use a complex approach and organize an offline event together with a digital project in co-creation with popular influencers. 
 
We knew that our target audience is very active in digital and social media, and from IKEA’s annual Life At Home Report we learned that for them home is a space that represents their identity and lifestyle. 
 
Our integrated campaign was kicked off by the event (an exhibition at the only street art museum in the world—Street Art Museum in St.Petersburg) and digital activation through a popular online-community OMANKO. And we also co-created series of videos #MyLifeMyStyle with influencers: street artist Pokras Lampas, the founder of the street culture festival Faces & Laces Dmitriy Oskes and the digital artist Zorian Istomin. It’s important to say that we did not limit ourselves to Moscow and St. Petersburg, but expanded our campaign to another 9 Russian cities: Ekaterinburg, Kazan, Nizhny Novgorod, Ufa, Omsk, Novosibirsk, Krasnodar, Rostov-on-Don, Sochi.

Results: more than 6,5 million views, 2000 comments in social media and 110 publications in key lifestyle media popular with millenials such as Daily.afisha, The Village and also by the traditional media.
 
The success of the campaign got recognized by IPRA Golden Award committee, that awarded us with a victory as ‘Launch of the new product’ of the year.", 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Susa', 'last_name': 'Agababyan', 'name': None, 'headline': 'UX Writer at Booking.com'}]}]
